# Template for packages/worker/.dev.vars (which is gitignored). Copy it to
# `.dev.vars` for local dev: `cp .dev.vars.example .dev.vars`.
#
# lopata loads `.dev.vars` on top of the wrangler `vars` (`.dev.vars` overrides
# `vars`), so the Worker boots locally without these secrets living in the
# generated wrangler.jsonc. Access doesn't exist locally; these are dummy values,
# never real credentials. Do NOT put real secrets here.
#
# Remote (stage/prod) provisioning is out-of-band: `wrangler secret put CF_API_TOKEN`
# and `wrangler secret put CF_ACCOUNT_ID`. See packages/worker/oblaka.ts.
CF_API_TOKEN=local-cf-api-token
CF_ACCOUNT_ID=local-cf-account-id
